Sri Lankan Economy to Recover in Second Quarter, IMF Says

-- B y   A n u s h a   O n d a a t j i e   a n d   A s a n t h a   S i r i m a n n e
-- 
2011-06-10T11:34:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-10/sri-lankan-economy-to-recover-in-second-quarter-imf-says.html
Sri Lanka ’s economy is expected to
bounce back in the second quarter of this year after being
affected in the first three months by floods, Brian Aitken, the
International Monetary Fund’s mission chief for the country,
said in  Colombo  today.  Sri Lanka’s consumer demand is picking up and there are no
signs that the island’s economy is overheating, Aitken said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anusha Ondaatjie in Colombo at 
